#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "Takes a long time to finish the installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    If you don't intend to tweak the settings, it is probably a waste of time\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:145
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Not suitable for networkless installations\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:151
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<e>Stage2</e> installs allow you to skip the bootstrap process and doing this\n"
"is fine if you are happy with the optimization settings that we chose\n"
"for your particular <e>stage2</e> tarball.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:157
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A <e>stage2</e> installation can only be performed when you have a working\n"
"Internet connection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "Stage2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "You don't need to bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "Faster than starting with stage1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "You can still tweak your settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot tweak as much as with a stage1"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:184
#, no-wrap
msgid "It's not the fastest way to install Gentoo"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid "You have to accept the optimizations we chose for the bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:199
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Choosing to go with a <e>stage3</e> allows for the fastest install of Gentoo\n"
"Linux, but also means that your base system will have the optimization\n"
"settings that we chose for you (which to be honest, are good settings\n"
"and were carefully chosen to enhance performance while maintaining\n"
"stability). <e>stage3</e> is also required if you want to install Gentoo using\n"
"prebuilt packages or without a network connection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "Stage3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "Fastest way to get a Gentoo base system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "Suitable for networkless installations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:222
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot tweak the base system - it's built already"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:226
#, no-wrap
msgid "You cannot brag about having used stage1 or stage2"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:231
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You might be interested to know that, if you decide to use different \n"
"optimization settings after having installed Gentoo, you will be able to \n"
"recompile your entire system with the new optimization settings.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:237
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now take a look at the available installation media.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "Gentoo LiveCDs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:247
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The <e>Gentoo LiveCDs</e> are bootable CDs which contain a\n"
"self-sustained Gentoo environment. They allow you to boot Linux from the CD.\n"
"During the boot process your hardware is detected and the appropriate drivers\n"
"are loaded. They are maintained by Gentoo developers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:254
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"All LiveCDs allow you to boot, set up networking, initialize your\n"
"partitions and start installing Gentoo from the Internet. However, some\n"
"LiveCDs also contain all necessary source code so you are able to install \n"
"Gentoo without a working network configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:261
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now what do these LiveCDs contain?\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:271
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This is a small, no-nonsense, bootable CD which sole purpose is to boot the \n"
"system, prepare the networking and continue with the Gentoo installation. It \n"
"does not contain any stages (or, in some cases, a single stage1 file), \n"
"source code or precompiled packages. For example the x86 variant of this \n"
"LiveCD can be found in the <path>universal</path> subdirectory and is called\n"
"<c>install-x86-minimal-2004.2.iso</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:281
#, no-wrap
msgid "Minimal LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:286
#, no-wrap
msgid "Smallest download"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "Suitable for a complete architecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:295
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    You can do a stage1, stage2 or stage3 by getting the stage tarball off the\n"
"    net\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:302
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Contains no stages, no Portage snapshot, no GRP packages and therefore not \n"
"    suitable for networkless installation\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Gentoo's Universal LiveCD is a bootable CD suitable to install Gentoo without\n"
"networking. It contains a stage1 and several stage3 tarballs (optimized for the\n"
"individual subarchitectures). For example the x86 variant of this CD is called\n"
"<c>install-x86-universal-2004.2.iso</c> and can be found in the\n"
"<path>universal</path> subdirectory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:323
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you take a closer look into <path>releases/x86/2004.2</path> you will see\n"
"that we also provide <e>Gentoo Package CDs</e> (in the <path>packagecd/</path>)\n"
"directory. This CD (which isn't bootable) only contains precompiled packages \n"
"and can be used to install software after a succesfull Gentoo Installation. To \n"
"install Gentoo, you only need the Universal LiveCD, but if you want \n"
"OpenOffice.org, Mozilla, KDE, GNOME etc. without having to compile every \n"
"single one of them, you need the Packages CD too. For example the i686\n"
"(a subarchitecture of x86) Packages CD is called <c>packages-i686-2004.2.iso</c>\n"
"and can be found in the appropriate subdirectory (i686).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:335
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You only need the Packages CD if you want to perform a stage3 with GRP\n"
"installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><th>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:341
#, no-wrap
msgid "Universal LiveCD with Packages CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid "Packages CD is optimized to your subarchitecture"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:351
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Packages CD provides precompiled packages for fast Gentoo installations\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:357
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Contains everything you need. You can even install without a network\n"
"    connection.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><table><tr><ti>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid "Huge download"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:371
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download, Burn and Boot a Gentoo LiveCD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:373
#, no-wrap
msgid "Downloading and Burning the LiveCDs"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:377
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You have chosen to use a Gentoo LiveCD. We'll first start by downloading and \n"
"burning the chosen LiveCD. We previously discussed the several available \n"
"LiveCDs, but where can you find them? \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:383
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can download any of the LiveCDs (and, if you want to, a Packages CD as\n"
"well) from one of our <uri link=\"/main/en/mirrors.xml\">mirrors</uri>. The\n"
"LiveCDs are located in the <path>releases/x86/2004.2/livecd</path> directory;\n"
"the Packages CDs are located in the <path>releases/x86/2004.2/packagecd</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:391
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inside that directory you'll find so-called ISO-files. Those are full CD images\n"
"which you can write on a CD-R.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:396
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In case you wonder if your downloaded file is corrupted or not, you can\n"
"check its MD5 checksum and compare it with the MD5 checksum we provide (such as\n"
"<path>install-x86-minimal-2004.2.iso.md5</path>). You can check the MD5 checksum\n"
"with the <c>md5sum</c> tool under Linux/Unix or <uri\n"
"link=\"http://www.etree.org/md5com.html\">md5sum</uri> for Windows.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Another way to check the validity of the downloaded file is to use GnuPG to\n"
"verify the cryptographic signature that we provide (the file ending with\n"
"<path>.asc</path>). Download the signature file and obtain the public key:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Obtaining the public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:410
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --keyserver pgp.mit.edu --recv-keys 17072058</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now verify the signature:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:417
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify the cryptographic signature"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><pre>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:418
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ <i>gpg --verify &lt;signature file&gt; &lt;downloaded iso&gt;</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:422
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To burn the downloaded ISO(s), you have to select raw-burning. How you\n"
"do this is highly program-dependent. We will discuss <c>cdrecord</c> and\n"
"<c>K3B</c> here; more information can be found in our <uri\n"
"link=\"/doc/en/faq.xml#isoburning\">Gentoo FAQ</uri>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:430
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With cdrecord, you simply type <c>cdrecord dev=/dev/hdc</c> (replace\n"
"    <path>/dev/hdc</path> with your CD-RW drive's device path) followed\n"
"    by the path to the ISO file :)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><ul><li>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:435
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    With K3B, select <c>Tools</c> &gt; <c>CD</c> &gt; <c>Burn Image</c>. Then\n"
"    you can locate your ISO file within the 'Image to Burn' area. Finally click\n"
"    <c>Start</c>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><title>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:444
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting the LiveCD(s)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><impo>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:448
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Read this whole subsection before continuing, as you will probably not have the\n"
"opportunity to read it before doing things later.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:453
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once you have burned your installation CDs, it is time to boot them.\n"
"Remove all CDs from your CD drives, reboot your system and enter the BIOS. \n"
"This is usually done by hitting DEL, F1 or ESC, depending on your BIOS. Inside \n"
"the BIOS, change the boot order so that the CD-ROM is tried before the hard \n"
"disk. This is often found under \"CMOS Setup\". If you don't do this, your system \n"
"will just reboot from the hard disk, ignoring the CD-ROM.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now place the installation CD in the CD-ROM drive (duh) and reboot. You\n"
"should see a fancy boot screen with the Gentoo Linux logo on it. At this\n"
"screen, you can hit Enter to begin the boot process with the default\n"
"boot options, or boot the LiveCD with custom boot options by specifying a \n"
"kernel followed by boot options and then hitting Enter. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:470
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Specifying a kernel? Yes, we provide several kernels on our LiveCDs. The\n"
"default one is <c>gentoo</c>. Other kernels are <c>smp</c>, which activates \n"
"support for multi-cpu systems and the <c>-nofb</c> variants which disable\n"
"framebuffer. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:477
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It is recommended that you select the <c>gentoo</c> or <c>gentoo-nofb</c>\n"
"kernels if you want to install Gentoo Linux with a 2.4 kernel or <c>smp</c> or\n"
"<c>smp-nofb</c> if you want to install Gentoo Linux with a 2.6 kernel. Otherwise\n"
"you might run into compatibility issues.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <sections><section><subsection><body><p>
#: en/handbook/2004.2/hb-install-x86-medium.xml:484
#, no-wrap
msgid "Below you'll find a short overview on the available kernels:\n"
msgstr ""

